cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the security concerns in Android app development and proposes a storyboard-based design methodology to address them. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the design methodology, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the user experience (UX) of the app, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper proposes a methodology for specification and verification of security properties, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
